name: Ctrl V / Control V
description: n computing, Control-V is a key stroke with a variety of uses including generation of a control character in ASCII code, also known as the synchronous idle (SYN) character. The key stroke is generated by pressing the V key while holding down the Ctrl key on a computer keyboard. For MacOS based systems, which lack a Ctrl key, the common replacement of using the ⌘ Cmd key does in fact work.
